            <bio>
               <p>
                  <bold>Esther Horn</bold> holds a master's degree in medieval English literature from Southwest Texas State University. While pursuing her degree she had the outstanding luck of securing a full time job in 1998 with an organization on campus: CALICO. She's been happily organizing its conferences, proofreading its articles, and trying to keep track of its members ever since. She had the pleasure of working with Robert Fischer in his capacity as Executive Director of CALICO until 2011 and now continuing to work with him in his capacity as Chair of Modern Languages.</p>
